column15: Inventors

column12: Apparatus and method for printing on a curved glass surface
column13: Embodiments of the invention are directed to systems and methods for printing on a convex or concave glass surface and for an apparatus for holding the one or more work pieces for printing. The invention operatively couples one or more curved pieces in a mounting fixture, wherein each of the one or more curved pieces comprise a convex surface or a concave surface. Furthermore, the invention accesses a flattened image of the convex outer surface or the concave inner surface of one or more generally curved pieces and disposes pigment on the convex surface or the concave surface of the one or more curved pieces according to the flattened image. Further embodiments may be directed towards printing on curved pieces such as glass eyes.
column15: DAVIS CHAD MATTHEW;;EPPLEY BRADLEY A

column15: MOSTOLLER MATTHEW EDWARD;;GINGRICH III;;EPPLEY NAZARETH WAYNE

column12: Jumper connector for a lighting assembly
column13: A jumper connector (24) for connecting lighting components (22) to one another includes a connector body (60) having a mating surface (66) configured to engage more than one lighting component (22), where the connector body (60) is configured to be secured to a substrate (28) by a fastener (78). The jumper connector (24) also includes a conductor held by the body (60), wherein the conductor is configured to be electrically connected to more than one lighting component (22) during the same manufacturing step in which the connector body (60) is secured to the substrate (28).

column12: JUMPER CONNECTOR FOR LIGHTING ASSEMBLY
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a jumper connector for a lighting assembly discharging heat quickly at low cost and easy to manufacture.

SOLUTION: The jumper connector (24) for connecting lighting components (22) to one another includes a connector body (60) having a mating surface (66) configured to engage two or more lighting components. The connector body is configured to be fixed to a substrate (28) by a fastener (78). The jumper connector also includes a conductor held by the connector body. The conductor is configured to be electrically connected with two or more lighting components during the same manufacturing process in which the connector body is fixed to the substrate.

column12: INTERFACE INFRASTRUCTURE FOR CREATING WEB SERVICE AND PERFORMING CONVERSATION
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide an interface infrastructure creating a Web Service and performing conversation.

SOLUTION: A web service name space relates to the infrastructure for realizing creation of various applications. The infrastructure provides a basis for constructing message base applications varied in scale and complication. The infrastructure or a framework provides an API for basic messaging, secure messaging, reliable messaging, and transaction type messaging. In some implementation forms, an associated API is factorized to layers in a name space by a method balancing utility, usability, extensibility, and a version property.
